[Property]
SidebarVisible
[PropertyType]
BYTE
[PropertyDescription]
Gets or sets whether the sidebar is visible. Use from Clarion: PDFViewerCOM_Ctrl{'SidebarVisible'} = 0  (0=hide, 1=show) Can be set before ViewerReady â€” applied automatically when viewer initializes.

[Property]
AnnotationsEnabled
[PropertyType]
BYTE
[PropertyDescription]
Gets or sets whether annotations are enabled. Use from Clarion: PDFViewerCOM_Ctrl{'AnnotationsEnabled'} = 0  (0=disable, 1=enable) Can be set before ViewerReady â€” applied automatically when viewer initializes.

[Property]
AllowHighlight
[PropertyType]
BYTE
[PropertyDescription]
Gets or sets whether the Highlight button is visible. Default: false. Must be explicitly set to true to enable highlighting.

[Property]
AllowNotes
[PropertyType]
BYTE
[PropertyDescription]
Gets or sets whether the Note button is visible. Default: false. Must be explicitly set to true to enable note annotations.

[Property]
AllowDrawing
[PropertyType]
BYTE
[PropertyDescription]
Gets or sets whether the Draw button is visible. Default: false. Must be explicitly set to true to enable drawing.

[Property]
AllowSaveAs
[PropertyType]
BYTE
[PropertyDescription]
Gets or sets whether the Save As (Download) button is visible. Default: true. Set to false to prevent users from saving the document.

[Property]
FilePath
[PropertyType]
STRING
[PropertyDescription]
File path to load when LoadFilePath() is called. Set this before calling LoadFilePath(). Workaround for Clarion late-binding which cannot pass parameters to COM methods.

[Property]
Base64Data
[PropertyType]
STRING
[PropertyDescription]
Base64-encoded PDF data to load when LoadBase64Data() is called. Workaround for Clarion late-binding which cannot pass parameters to COM methods.

[Property]
SourceBase64
[PropertyType]
STRING
[PropertyDescription]
Gets the original PDF bytes as Base64 (from LoadFile or LoadBase64). Store this alongside annotation JSON to enable editable round-trips. In Clarion: OrigB64 = PDFViewerCOM_Ctrl{'SourceBase64'}

[Property]
AnnotationsData
[PropertyType]
STRING
[PropertyDescription]
Annotation JSON to import when ImportAnnotationsData() is called. Set this before calling ImportAnnotationsData(). In Clarion: PDFViewerCOM_Ctrl{'AnnotationsData'} = clip(AnnotJsonField)

[Property]
LoadType
[PropertyType]
STRING
[PropertyDescription]
Gets how the current document was loaded: 'base64' (LoadBase64/LoadBase64Data), 'file' (LoadFile/LoadFilePath), or 'url' (LoadUrl). Use in Clarion to guard ImportAnnotationsData() calls â€” only restore annotations when LoadType = 'base64', so disk/URL loads start clean. In Clarion: lType = PDFViewerCOM_Ctrl{'LoadType'}

[Method]
GetIsReady
[MethodDescription]
Gets whether WebView2 is fully initialized and ready.

[Method]
GetLastError
[MethodDescription]
Gets the last error message.

[Method]
GetSource
[MethodDescription]
Gets the current source URL or file path.

[Method]
GetCurrentPage
[MethodDescription]
Gets the current page number (1-based).

[Method]
GetPageCount
[MethodDescription]
Gets the total number of pages in the PDF.

[Method]
GetZoomLevel
[MethodDescription]
Gets the zoom level (1.0 = 100%).

[Method]
SetZoomLevel
[MethodDescription]
Sets the zoom level (1.0 = 100%).
[Parameter]
value
[ParameterType]
REAL
[ParameterDescription]
The zoom level to set

[Method]
GetSidebarVisible
[MethodDescription]
Gets whether the sidebar (thumbnails/bookmarks) is visible.

[Method]
SetSidebarVisible
[MethodDescription]
Sets whether the sidebar (thumbnails/bookmarks) is visible.
[Parameter]
value
[ParameterType]
BYTE
[ParameterDescription]
True to show sidebar, false to hide

[Method]
GetAnnotationsEnabled
[MethodDescription]
Gets whether annotations are enabled.

[Method]
SetAnnotationsEnabled
[MethodDescription]
Sets whether annotations are enabled.
[Parameter]
value
[ParameterType]
BYTE
[ParameterDescription]
True to enable annotations, false to disable

[Method]
LoadFilePath
[MethodDescription]
Load the PDF file stored in the FilePath property. Use this from Clarion: set FilePath property first, then call LoadFilePath().

[Method]
LoadBase64Data
[MethodDescription]
Load the PDF from the Base64Data property. Use this from Clarion: set Base64Data property first, then call LoadBase64Data().

[Method]
LoadFile
[MethodDescription]
Load a PDF file from a file path.
[Parameter]
filePath
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
Full path to the PDF file

[Method]
LoadUrl
[MethodDescription]
Load a PDF from a URL.
[Parameter]
url
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
URL to the PDF document

[Method]
LoadBase64
[MethodDescription]
Load a PDF from Base64-encoded data.
[Parameter]
base64Data
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
Base64-encoded PDF data

[Method]
CloseDocument
[MethodDescription]
Close the current PDF document.

[Method]
GoToPage
[MethodDescription]
Navigate to a specific page.
[Parameter]
pageNumber
[ParameterType]
LONG
[ParameterDescription]
Page number (1-based)

[Method]
NextPage
[MethodDescription]
Navigate to the next page.

[Method]
PreviousPage
[MethodDescription]
Navigate to the previous page.

[Method]
FirstPage
[MethodDescription]
Navigate to the first page.

[Method]
LastPage
[MethodDescription]
Navigate to the last page.

[Method]
ZoomIn
[MethodDescription]
Zoom in by a standard increment.

[Method]
ZoomOut
[MethodDescription]
Zoom out by a standard increment.

[Method]
SetZoom
[MethodDescription]
Set zoom level to a specific percentage.
[Parameter]
percentage
[ParameterType]
REAL
[ParameterDescription]
Zoom percentage (e.g., 100 for 100%)

[Method]
FitWidth
[MethodDescription]
Fit the page width to the viewer width.

[Method]
FitPage
[MethodDescription]
Fit the entire page in the viewer.

[Method]
ActualSize
[MethodDescription]
Reset zoom to 100%.

[Method]
Search
[MethodDescription]
Search for text in the document.
[Parameter]
searchText
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
Text to search for
[Parameter]
caseSensitive
[ParameterType]
BYTE
[ParameterDescription]
Whether search is case-sensitive

[Method]
FindNext
[MethodDescription]
Find the next occurrence of the search text.

[Method]
FindPrevious
[MethodDescription]
Find the previous occurrence of the search text.

[Method]
ClearSearch
[MethodDescription]
Clear search highlighting.

[Method]
HighlightSelection
[MethodDescription]
Add a highlight annotation to the current selection.
[Parameter]
color
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
Highlight color (e.g., "#FFFF00" for yellow)

[Method]
AddNote
[MethodDescription]
Add a text note annotation at the specified position.
[Parameter]
pageNumber
[ParameterType]
LONG
[ParameterDescription]
Page number (1-based)
[Parameter]
x
[ParameterType]
REAL
[ParameterDescription]
X coordinate
[Parameter]
y
[ParameterType]
REAL
[ParameterDescription]
Y coordinate
[Parameter]
text
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
Note text content

[Method]
EnableDrawing
[MethodDescription]
Enable drawing mode for freehand annotations.
[Parameter]
color
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
Stroke color
[Parameter]
width
[ParameterType]
LONG
[ParameterDescription]
Stroke width in pixels

[Method]
DisableDrawing
[MethodDescription]
Disable drawing mode.

[Method]
ClearAnnotations
[MethodDescription]
Delete all annotations on the current page.

[Method]
ExportAnnotations
[MethodDescription]
Trigger annotation export. Result is delivered asynchronously via the AnnotationsExported event. In Clarion: PDFViewerCOM_Ctrl{'ExportAnnotations'} â€” handle AnnotationsExported event for the JSON.

[Method]
ImportAnnotationsData
[MethodDescription]
Import annotations from the AnnotationsData property. In Clarion: PDFViewerCOM_Ctrl{'ImportAnnotationsData'}

[Method]
ImportAnnotations
[MethodDescription]
Import annotations from JSON.
[Parameter]
annotationsJson
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
JSON string containing annotations

[Method]
Print
[MethodDescription]
Print the document using the system print dialog.

[Method]
SaveAs
[MethodDescription]
Download/save the current PDF (including annotations if any).
[Parameter]
filePath
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
Destination file path

[Method]
SaveAsBase64
[MethodDescription]
Save the current view with all annotations (highlights, notes, drawings) as a Base64-encoded PDF. The result is returned asynchronously via the SaveAsBase64Ready event. Use this when the document was loaded via LoadBase64 (e.g., from a StringTheory object).

[Method]
ToggleSidebar
[MethodDescription]
Toggle the sidebar visibility (thumbnails/bookmarks panel).

[Method]
ShowThumbnails
[MethodDescription]
Show the thumbnails panel in the sidebar.

[Method]
ShowBookmarks
[MethodDescription]
Show the bookmarks/outline panel in the sidebar.

[Method]
RotateClockwise
[MethodDescription]
Rotate the current page clockwise by 90 degrees.

[Method]
RotateCounterClockwise
[MethodDescription]
Rotate the current page counter-clockwise by 90 degrees.

[Method]
Navigate
[MethodDescription]
Navigate to a URL (base WebView2 functionality).
[Parameter]
url
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
The URL to navigate to

[Method]
Refresh
[MethodDescription]
Refresh the current page.

[Method]
ExecuteScript
[MethodDescription]
Execute JavaScript code in the current page.
[Parameter]
script
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
The JavaScript code to execute

[Method]
PostMessage
[MethodDescription]
Post a message to JavaScript. JavaScript can receive via: window.chrome.webview.addEventListener('message', handler)
[Parameter]
message
[ParameterType]
STRING
[ParameterDescription]
The message to send (string or JSON)

[Method]
About
[MethodDescription]
Displays control name and version information in a MessageBox.

